Police have launched a search party for Lucia Tseiso (43) of Ga-Kobo Village in Moletji after she allegedly went missing on 30 March.
Provincial Police Spokesperson Moatshe Ngoepe indicated that the woman is originally from Lesotho and was employed as a shopkeeper at Ga-Kobo.
She allegedly left her workplace on 30 March to visit her sister in Gauteng but she never reached her destination, according to Ngoepe.
Since then no one knows her whereabouts and the type of clothes she was last wearing is unknown.
Police have conducted search operations at relatives and friends without any success.
Anyone with information is requested to contact Colonel Mogale on 071 479 2329 or report to the nearest Police station.
Story: RC Myburgh